__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Regenerable pipeline outputs (rebuild with `python run.py build`)
data/raw/
data/assets/
data/kb.sqlite
data/kb.json

# Phase-2 question bank (rebuild with `python run.py questions`)
data/questions.sqlite
data/questions.json
data/questions.json.*
# France per-option banks (rebuild with `python run.py fr`); the durable source is
# src/fr/seed_fr.py and the deployable bundle is committed under web/fr/.
data/questions.fr_*.sqlite
# Germany bank (rebuild with `python run.py questions --country DE`); the durable
# source is the official ELWIS catalogue, ingested verbatim by src/questions/elwis.py.
data/questions.de.sqlite
data/questions.de.json

# Subagent-drafting intermediates (regenerable: emit / verify-emit / merge),
# all languages. The durable inputs — data/draft_answers/ and data/verdicts/ —
# ARE committed, so the approved prose bank rebuilds via `subagent_draft.py ingest`.
# data/seed_review.json (the manual-review ledger) is likewise committed: it
# restores hand-set approvals/rejections that the regenerable DB would lose.
data/draft_jobs*.json
data/verify_jobs*.json
data/verdicts*.json
# EN translation intermediates (durable: translate_answers/ + translate_verdicts/).
data/translate_jobs.json
data/translate_verify.json
# Figure-question intermediates (durable: figure_answers/ + figure_verdicts/ —
# committed so the night-lighting bank rebuilds via `subagent_figures.py ingest`).
data/figure_jobs*.json
data/figure_verify*.json
data/figure_verdicts*.json
# Anki/GIFT exports: the working copies under data/anki/ + data/gift/ are
# throwaway (rebuild with `python tools/anki.py export` / `tools/gift.py export`).
# The web/anki/ + web/gift/ copies ARE committed below so GitHub Pages can serve
# them as downloads (public-domain data).
data/anki/
data/gift/

# Static-player data bundle (rebuild with `python run.py web`). NOW COMMITTED so
# GitHub Pages can serve it (the data is public-domain law). Regenerate with
# `python run.py web` after changing the bank, then commit the diff.
#   web/questions.json, web/questions.<lang>.json, web/languages.json, web/assets/
#   web/anki/boat-permit.<lang>.{apkg,tsv}  (the in-page Anki download)
#   web/gift/boat-permit.<lang>.gift        (the in-page Moodle/GIFT download)
